BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:proimagenes-fdc-estimulos-automaticos-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261211
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261212
SUMMARY:Deadline: Proimagenes Colombia: FDC 2026 Estimulos Automaticos
DESCRIPTION:The Fondo para el Desarrollo Cinematografico\, created by Colom
 bia's Law 814 of 2003 and administered by Proimagenes Colombia\, channels 
 at least 70 percent of its resources into film production. The automatic s
 timuli are the non-competitive strand: rather than pitching against other 
 projects\, applicants qualify by meeting defined criteria. Six lines are o
 pen for 2026\, all closing 11 December 2026: film distribution in theatres
 \, Colombian shorts and features selected for approved festivals\, films n
 ominated for approved awards\, projects selected for approved industry enc
 ounters\, individuals selected for approved training workshops and advisor
 ies\, and promotion of national features or coproductions of at least 70 m
 inutes premiering in 2026. A separate competitive strand (estimulos por co
 ncurso) runs 17 modalities on its own calendar. ELIGIBILITY IS RESTRICTED:
  Colombian natural persons and Colombian legal entities\, though a Colombi
 an company may have a foreign legal representative. Contact convocatoriafd
 c@proimagenescolombia.com.\n\nOrganisation: Proimagenes Colombia (Fondo pa
 ra el Desarrollo Cinematografico)\nLocation: Colombia. Open to Colombian n
 atural persons and Colombian legal entities only.\nAward: Six automatic-st
 imulus lines drawn from the FDC's 2026 pool of roughly COP 21\,900 million
  (around USD 5.5 million). The feature film promotion line alone carries C
 OP 3\,620 million. Amounts per award are set per line. No application fee.
 \nDuration: Applies to activities taking place during 2026\; automatic sti
 muli are awarded on qualification rather than by competition.\n\nMore: htt
 ps://www.convocatoriafdc.com/estimulos-automaticos?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.convocatoriafdc.com/estimulos-automaticos?utm_source=artifi
 cialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Colombia. Open to Colombian natural persons and Colombian legal en
 tities only.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fifm-atlas-workshops-post-production-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: Marrakech IFF: Atlas Workshops 2026 (Films in Shooting or
  Post-Production)
DESCRIPTION:The Atlas Workshops are the Marrakech International Film Festiv
 al's industry and talent-development programme\, running since 2018 and no
 w in its 9th edition. This track is for feature films already in shooting 
 or post-production. Selected teams get personalised mentoring tailored to 
 each project across scriptwriting\, production\, distribution\, editing an
 d scoring\, plus access to the festival's industry network\, and compete f
 or cash prizes decided by a dedicated jury. ELIGIBILITY: directors and pro
 ducers who are from\, or in the diaspora of\, the Arab world or the Africa
 n continent\, working on their first\, second or third feature (fiction\, 
 documentary or animation)\, with a production company attached. Open acros
 s that whole region\, not restricted to Morocco. There is a separate Proje
 cts in Development track whose deadline (6 July 2026) has already passed f
 or this edition. Deadline 31 August 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Festival Intern
 ational du Film de Marrakech (Atlas Workshops)\nLocation: Online in Octobe
 r 2026\, then onsite in Marrakech\, Morocco\, 22-26 November 2026\, alongs
 ide the Marrakech International Film Festival.\nAward: No application fee.
  Participation in the online and onsite programme is covered. Cash prizes 
 are awarded by a dedicated jury at the close of the Workshops\; the festiv
 al does not publish the prize amounts on the call page.\nDuration: Five-da
 y online programme in October 2026\, followed by a five-day onsite program
 me 22-26 November 2026.\n\nMore: https://atlasateliers.marrakech-festival.
 com/en/call-for-applications?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
URL:https://atlasateliers.marrakech-festival.com/en/call-for-applications?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Online in October 2026\, then onsite in Marrakech\, Morocco\, 22-2
 6 November 2026\, alongside the Marrakech International Film Festival.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fifm-atlas-station-producers-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: Marrakech IFF: Atlas Station 2026 (Producers Track)
DESCRIPTION:Atlas Station is the Marrakech International Film Festival's pr
 ofessional development strand running alongside the Atlas Workshops\, aime
 d at building the Moroccan film industry. The producers track offers struc
 tured mentoring\, industry sessions and access to the festival's internati
 onal network during the 9th edition. ELIGIBILITY IS RESTRICTED: open to Mo
 roccan producers only\, not to international applicants. Deadline 31 Augus
 t 2026. See also the Atlas Station short film track (deadline 14 September
  2026) and the internationally open Atlas Workshops track for films in sho
 oting or post-production.\n\nOrganisation: Festival International du Film 
 de Marrakech (Atlas Workshops)\nLocation: Online in October 2026\, then on
 site in Marrakech\, Morocco\, 22-26 November 2026. Open to Moroccan produc
 ers only.\nAward: No application fee. Participation in the online and onsi
 te professional programme is covered.\nDuration: Five-day online programme
  in October 2026\, followed by a five-day onsite programme 22-26 November 
 2026.\n\nMore: https://atlasateliers.marrakech-festival.com/en/call-for-ap
 plications?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://atlasateliers.marrakech-festival.com/en/call-for-applications?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Online in October 2026\, then onsite in Marrakech\, Morocco\, 22-2
 6 November 2026. Open to Moroccan producers only.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fifm-atlas-station-short-film-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260914
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260915
SUMMARY:Deadline: Marrakech IFF: Atlas Station 2026 (Short Film Track)
DESCRIPTION:The short film strand of Atlas Station\, the Marrakech Internat
 ional Film Festival's professional development programme for the Moroccan 
 film industry\, running alongside the 9th Atlas Workshops. Selected direct
 ors receive mentoring and industry access during the online and onsite ses
 sions. ELIGIBILITY IS RESTRICTED: open to Moroccan directors with a short 
 film in shooting or post-production that has not yet premiered. Not open t
 o international applicants. Deadline 14 September 2026.\n\nOrganisation: F
 estival International du Film de Marrakech (Atlas Workshops)\nLocation: On
 line in October 2026\, then onsite in Marrakech\, Morocco\, 22-26 November
  2026. Open to Moroccan directors only.\nAward: No application fee. Partic
 ipation in the online and onsite professional programme is covered.\nDurat
 ion: Five-day online programme in October 2026\, followed by a five-day on
 site programme 22-26 November 2026.\n\nMore: https://atlasateliers.marrake
 ch-festival.com/en/call-for-applications?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrant
 desk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://atlasateliers.marrakech-festival.com/en/call-for-applications?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Online in October 2026\, then onsite in Marrakech\, Morocco\, 22-2
 6 November 2026. Open to Moroccan directors only.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:medienboard-immersive-2027-r1@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261027
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261028
SUMMARY:Deadline: Medienboard Berlin-Brandenburg: Innovative Audiovisual Co
 ntent / Immersive (2027 Round 1)
DESCRIPTION:Medienboard's Immersive strand funds the development and produc
 tion of immersive and innovative audiovisual content: virtual\, augmented 
 and mixed-reality experiences plus multi-platform and cross-media projects
 \, and it also supports festival presentation of XR and innovative audiovi
 sual work. This is the most directly creative-technology-facing German reg
 ional fund open to organisations. The applicant must be a developer or ind
 ependent producer with a registered company seat in Berlin-Brandenburg or 
 elsewhere in Germany\, which rules out individual artists without a compan
 y\; international partners can participate as co-producers but cannot lead
 . THE PROCESS IS GATED: applicants submit a one-page project summary rough
 ly six weeks before the deadline\, then must hold an application meeting w
 ith a funding executive about two weeks before the deadline\, and only aft
 er that meeting is portal access granted. Plan backwards from the deadline
  accordingly. The 2026 rounds closed on 3 February\, 28 April and 21 July 
 2026\; the next live deadline is 27 October 2026\, feeding the first commi
 ttee of 2027 with decisions announced in week 5 of 2027\, a decision lag o
 f about three months. The DIGI.TALE sub-strand is restricted to students o
 f Film University Babelsberg KONRAD WOLF and DFFB.\n\nOrganisation: Medien
 board Berlin-Brandenburg GmbH\nLocation: Berlin-Brandenburg\, Germany. A B
 erlin-Brandenburg regional effect applies.\nAward: FLAG\, UNVERIFIED: amou
 nts are not stated on the public scheme page. Financial terms\, grant-vers
 us-conditionally-repayable-loan status\, own-contribution percentage and t
 he Berlin-Brandenburg regional spend requirement are set out only in the d
 ownloadable guideline PDF (Merkblatt Innovative Audiovisuelle Inhalte). No
  application fee indicated. Confirm figures and whether support is a grant
  or a repayable loan before applying.\nDuration: Project-based\; developme
 nt and production phases are funded separately.\n\nMore: https://www.medie
 nboard.de/en/funding/immersive/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://www.medienboard.de/en/funding/immersive/?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin-Brandenburg\, Germany. A Berlin-Brandenburg regional effect
  applies.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bfi-national-lottery-discovery-feature-funding-2026@artificialnouveau.g
 ithub.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260813
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260814
SUMMARY:Deadline: BFI National Lottery Discovery Feature Funding (Debut Fic
 tion Features)
DESCRIPTION:Discovery is the debut-director production strand of the BFI Fi
 lmmaking Fund\, awarding up to GBP 1 million towards fiction features budg
 eted between GBP 1 million and GBP 3.5 million. It backs first-time featur
 e directors working alongside experienced producers\, and is structured so
  creative risk sits with a team rather than a lone filmmaker. ELIGIBILITY:
  applications must be made through a limited company registered and centra
 lly managed in the UK\, so unincorporated individuals cannot apply. A dedi
 cated lead producer with an established track record must submit\, and tha
 t producer must be someone other than the writer or director. The director
  must be making their first fiction feature\, meaning no prior feature at 
 or above a GBP 1 million budget and no prior commercial UK or Ireland thea
 trical distribution of a fiction feature. At least two people must be cred
 ited across the writer\, producer and director roles\, all aged 18 or over
  and not in full-time education. Projects need a fully developed script an
 d a runtime of at least 70 minutes. LIMITS: one application per production
  company\, producer and director per round\, and applications must arrive 
 at least 20 weeks before the proposed first day of principal photography. 
 ROUNDS: Round 2 closes at 5pm on Thursday 13 August 2026. Round 3 opens Th
 ursday 12 November 2026 and closes Wednesday 16 December 2026. Successful 
 applicants must publicly credit BFI National Lottery support.\n\nOrganisat
 ion: British Film Institute (BFI Filmmaking Fund\, National Lottery)\nLoca
 tion: United Kingdom (applications must come from a limited company regist
 ered and centrally managed in the UK)\nAward: Up to GBP 1\,000\,000 of Nat
 ional Lottery funding towards a fiction feature with a production budget b
 etween GBP 1\,000\,000 and GBP 3\,500\,000. No application fee.\nDuration:
  Single production award\; apply at least 20 weeks before the first day of
  principal photography. Decisions in principle within roughly 12 weeks of 
 the round closing.\n\nMore: https://www.bfi.org.uk/get-funding-support/cre
 ate-films-tv-or-new-formats-storytelling/bfi-filmmaking-fund-discovery-imp
 act-feature-funding?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refer
 ral
URL:https://www.bfi.org.uk/get-funding-support/create-films-tv-or-new-forma
 ts-storytelling/bfi-filmmaking-fund-discovery-impact-feature-funding?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:United Kingdom (applications must come from a limited company regi
 stered and centrally managed in the UK)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bfi-national-lottery-creative-challenge-fund-round-2-2026@artificialnou
 veau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260921
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260922
SUMMARY:Deadline: BFI National Lottery Creative Challenge Fund (Round Two)
DESCRIPTION:The Creative Challenge Fund does not fund films directly. It fu
 nds the organisations that run project-development programmes for UK creat
 ives working on narrative\, documentary or animation features\, or on narr
 ative immersive media projects. The BFI's stated aim is to decentralise de
 velopment away from a small number of London-centric gatekeepers and build
  a wider\, more resilient ecosystem of talent-development providers across
  the UK\, with a recently added emphasis on independent producers. ELIGIBI
 LITY: only legally constituted UK-based organisations may apply. Individua
 l filmmakers seeking development money should look to the BFI Filmmaking F
 und's Development strand instead. TIMING: Round One closed in March 2026 a
 nd has made its first awards. Round Two closes Monday 21 September 2026\, 
 with funded programme activity required to begin between 1 January and 30 
 June 2027. NOTE: award amounts are not published on the fund page. Success
 ful applicants must prominently credit BFI National Lottery support.\n\nOr
 ganisation: British Film Institute (BFI National Lottery)\nLocation: Unite
 d Kingdom (UK-based organisations running development programmes for UK cr
 eatives)\nAward: Award amounts are not published on the fund page. No appl
 ication fee.\nDuration: Funded programme activity must start between 1 Jan
 uary and 30 June 2027 and\, in most cases\, be delivered within 12 months 
 unless the applicant is running multiple editions.\n\nMore: https://www.bf
 i.org.uk/get-funding-support/create-films-tv-or-new-formats-storytelling/b
 fi-national-lottery-creative-challenge-fund?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.bfi.org.uk/get-funding-support/create-films-tv-or-new-forma
 ts-storytelling/bfi-national-lottery-creative-challenge-fund?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:United Kingdom (UK-based organisations running development program
 mes for UK creatives)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bloomberg-green-docs-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260814
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260815
SUMMARY:Deadline: Bloomberg Green Docs Competition 2026 (Short Climate Docu
 mentary)
DESCRIPTION:The Bloomberg Green Docs competition is open to all eligible fi
 lmmakers competing for a $25\,000 grand prize for a short climate document
 ary. The call seeks films that explore our climate future and reveal the w
 orld we are making today: ecosystems being restored\, tomorrow's zero-carb
 on communities being formed\, and habitat extremes warning of cascading cl
 imate consequences. REQUIREMENTS: films must address the urgency of climat
 e change and run under 10 minutes including credits. The jury awards a $25
 \,000 grand prize\, announced at the Bloomberg Green Docs Film Festival in
  New York City on 22 September 2026\, where the top five documentaries wil
 l be screened. Check the official rules on the competition site for eligib
 ility details. DEADLINE: submissions accepted through 14 August 2026.\n\nO
 rganisation: Bloomberg Green\nLocation: Open call for filmmakers (see elig
 ibility rules on the site)\; festival screening in New York City\, USA.\nA
 ward: $25\,000 grand prize awarded by a jury\; the top five documentaries 
 screen at the Bloomberg Green Docs Film Festival in New York City. No entr
 y fee stated.\nDuration: Winner announced at the festival on 22 September 
 2026\n\nMore: https://www.bloomberg.com/greendocs/?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.bloomberg.com/greendocs/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantd
 esk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Open call for filmmakers (see eligibility rules on the site)\; fes
 tival screening in New York City\, USA.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:corridor-daisy-chain-commission-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260803
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260804
SUMMARY:Deadline: Corridor: DAISY CHAIN Artist Commission (Adur\, West Suss
 ex)
DESCRIPTION:Corridor seeks a socially-engaged artist based in the South Eas
 t of England working with moving image / lens-based media for DAISY CHAIN\
 , marking the 60th anniversary of Vera Chytilova's experimental film Daisi
 es (1966). The commissioned artist will work with a group of LGBTQIA+ youn
 g people aged 15-26 in Adur (West Sussex) to co-create new artworks: a 2-3
  minute moving image work and a series of 2D collage or mixed media artwor
 ks for public exhibition and screenings. DAISY CHAIN commissions six new a
 rtist moving image works overall (three England-based artists working with
  older women\, young women and LGBTQIA+ youth\; three artists in Czechia)\
 , developed in partnership with the National Film Museum in Prague (NaFilM
 ) and Brighton-based videoclub\, with results toured across England and Cz
 echia in 2027. EXPECTATIONS: devise about eight hands-on workshops incorpo
 rating film\, collage and mixed media (participants won't necessarily have
  an arts background)\; participate in 4-6 online peer sessions on collabor
 ative practice led by artist Annis Joslin\; complete exhibition-ready artw
 orks on time and to budget\; maintain a transparent dialogue on authorship
  with participants. Artists must have a participatory practice and experie
 nce of working creatively with young people. Note: to create a safe space\
 , workshops will not be publicly labelled as LGBTQIA+. FEE: GBP 4\,200 inc
 l. VAT plus travel and a materials budget. TIMELINE: shortlist notified 7 
 August\, online interviews 12 August 2026\; launch event in Adur/Worthing 
 March 2027. DEADLINE: 10am\, 3 August 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Corridor Proj
 ects\nLocation: Adur and Worthing\, West Sussex\, UK. Open to a socially-e
 ngaged artist based in the South East of England working with moving image
  / lens-based media.\nAward: GBP 4\,200 artist fee (inclusive of VAT) paid
  in instalments\, plus travel\, and an additional budget for materials for
  creative production\, workshops and exhibition outputs (e.g. print). No a
 pplication fee.\nDuration: September 2026 to July 2027: workshops Septembe
 r-January\, post-production to February 2027\, UK and Czech tour March-Jul
 y 2027\n\nMore: https://www.corridorprojects.org.uk/daisy-chain-commission
 ?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.corridorprojects.org.uk/daisy-chain-commission?utm_source=a
 rtificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Adur and Worthing\, West Sussex\, UK. Open to a socially-engaged a
 rtist based in the South East of England working with moving image / lens-
 based media.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:nebraska-arts-council-artist-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261117
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261118
SUMMARY:Deadline: Nebraska Arts Council: Individual Artist Fellowship 2026 
 (Performing Arts)
DESCRIPTION:The Nebraska Arts Council's Individual Artist Fellowship awards
  up to $5\,000 for a one-year period to support professional development: 
 creating new work\, presentations\, training and/or research. The fellowsh
 ip rotates among three umbrella categories\; the 2026 round accepts Perfor
 ming Arts applications in theater/playwriting\, choreography\, filmmaking/
 screenwriting\, and music/sound. ELIGIBILITY: Nebraska resident for at lea
 st 24 months before application\, remaining resident during the fellowship
  year (attestation required)\; 19 or older\; not enrolled in an undergradu
 ate program in the discipline applied for (graduate and certificate progra
 ms allowed)\; applicants must be the originator of the submitted work\, no
 t an interpreter. Previous winners may reapply after three years with new 
 work if prior grant requirements were completed. SUBMISSION: artist biogra
 phy\, artist statement (name redacted\; themes\, influences\, techniques)\
 , and five work samples with descriptions or synopses. Questions: meagan.d
 ion@nebraska.gov. DEADLINE: 17 November 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Nebraska Ar
 ts Council\nLocation: Nebraska\, USA. Applicants must have been Nebraska r
 esidents for at least 24 months before applying and remain residents durin
 g the fellowship year.\nAward: Up to $5\,000 for a one-year fellowship sup
 porting professional development\, including the creation of new art\, pre
 sentations\, training and/or research. No application fee.\nDuration: One-
 year fellowship period\n\nMore: https://www.artscouncil.nebraska.gov/apply
 /individual-artist-fellowship/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_m
 edium=referral
URL:https://www.artscouncil.nebraska.gov/apply/individual-artist-fellowship
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Nebraska\, USA. Applicants must have been Nebraska residents for a
 t least 24 months before applying and remain residents during the fellowsh
 ip year.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:berlinale-talents-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260902
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260903
SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlinale Talents 2027 (Berlin International Film Festiva
 l)
DESCRIPTION:Berlinale Talents is the Berlin International Film Festival's t
 alent-development program: a week of workshops\, the Talents Lab and the T
 alent Project Market during the February 2027 Berlinale\, plus access to t
 he festival's industry network. ELIGIBILITY: international working film pr
 ofessionals with at least 1 feature\, 2 shorts\, or a widely screened or s
 treamed series\, across 15+ disciplines including directing\, sound design
 \, editing\, production\, cinematography and screenwriting. Participation 
 itself is free\; there is a EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early b
 ird before 19 August 2026) and travel and accommodation are not covered. D
 eadline 2 September 2026\, 12:00 CEST. Apply via the Berlinale Talents por
 tal.\n\nOrganisation: Berlinale / Berlin International Film Festival\nLoca
 tion: Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open inter
 nationally.\nAward: Free participation in the week-long professional progr
 am (Summit workshops\, Talents Lab\, Talent Project Market\, industry netw
 orking). NO stipend\; travel and accommodation are self-covered (national 
 film institutes often fund this\; Netherlands-based filmmakers can approac
 h the Netherlands Film Fund). EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early
  bird before 19 August 2026).\nDuration: One week during the Berlinale\, F
 ebruary 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm
 _source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open int
 ernationally.
END:VEVENT
