UID:insideout-refocus-fund-postproduction-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260722
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260723
SUMMARY:Deadline: Inside Out RE:Focus Fund Post-Production Grants 2026
DESCRIPTION:Established in 2018 through a lead gift from Martha McCain\, In
 side Out's RE:Focus Fund addresses industry inequities by providing direct
  financial support to women\, non-binary\, and/or trans filmmakers telling
  2SLGBTQ+ stories. Launched in 2019\, the RE:Focus Fund Post-Production Gr
 ants support the post-production and promotion of short and feature films.
  Applications for the 2026 round open 29 June 2026. ELIGIBILITY: women\, n
 on-binary\, and/or trans filmmakers whose projects tell 2SLGBTQ+ stories\;
  per the FAQ\, international projects may be eligible to apply. The reques
 ted funding amount is determined by the applicant\, and unsuccessful appli
 cants can request feedback and reapply the following year. Inside Out also
  runs other RE:Focus initiatives\, including a new Residency program for f
 irst-time feature filmmakers facing intersectional barriers. KEY DATES: su
 bmissions open 29 June 2026\, close 22 July 2026\, with notifications by 1
 5 August 2026. Apply and read the FAQ via the Eventival page linked from t
 he RE:Focus Fund site\; questions to industry@insideout.ca.\n\nOrganisatio
 n: Inside Out (Toronto 2SLGBTQ+ Film Festival)\nLocation: Toronto\, Canada
  (Inside Out is a Canadian organisation\; international projects may apply
 \, see FAQ)\nAward: Post-production grant funding to support the completio
 n and promotion of short and feature films\; the requested amount is set b
 y the applicant (see the FAQ 'How much funding can I request?'). Since 201
 8 the RE:Focus Fund has distributed more than CAD 300\,000 in grants and p
 rograms. No application fee.\nDuration: One-off post-production grant\n\nM
 ore: https://insideout.ca/initiatives/re-focus-fund/?utm_source=artificial
 nouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://insideout.ca/initiatives/re-focus-fund/?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Toronto\, Canada (Inside Out is a Canadian organisation\; internat
 ional projects may apply\, see FAQ)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:100-voices-of-florida-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260920
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260921
SUMMARY:Deadline: 100 Voices of Florida Film Grant
DESCRIPTION:100 Voices of Florida is a grant for filmmakers and screenwrite
 rs that awards up to USD 5\,000 in unrestricted funds\, which winners can 
 use for finishing funds\, festival submission fees\, cast and crew reimbur
 sements\, production\, or anything else. Applicants submit either a short 
 film (under twenty minutes) or a script (twenty pages or less)\; films in 
 other languages must include accurate English subtitles\, and scripts must
  be in English. The grant is open to writers\, directors\, and producers w
 ho are at least 18 years old\, and creative teams may submit\, though only
  one entrant receives the award. A panel of judges with professional filmm
 aking experience evaluates entries\, and the winner also receives a meetin
 g with an industry professional. The deadline for the current cycle is Sep
 tember 20\, 2026.\n\nOrganisation: 100 Voices of Florida\nLocation: Florid
 a\, United States\nAward: Up to USD 5\,000 (unrestricted) USD 25 applicati
 on fee with a Florida connection\, USD 35 without\nDuration: One-time gran
 t\n\nMore: https://www.100vof.com/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.100vof.com/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_mediu
 m=referral
LOCATION:Florida\, United States
END:VEVENT
