UID:small-file-media-festival-2026-call-for-work@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260701
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260702
SUMMARY:Deadline: Small File Media Festival 2026 - Call for Work
DESCRIPTION:The Small File Media Festival 2026 invites moving-image submiss
 ions under the theme "Can Small Files Save the World?" -- a call for artho
 use\, video work\, glitch aesthetics\, punk\, sci-fi\, narrative\, and doc
 umentary work made with a small-file mindset. This year the festival espec
 ially welcomes small-scale experiments with narrative and documentary. The
  festival frames Small File Ecomedia as a political and ecological interve
 ntion: small files function in regions with precarious infrastructure\, ci
 rcumvent bandwidth imperialism and surveillance\, and expose the environme
 ntal cost of mainstream online video. WHAT THEY WANT: craftily composed\, 
 elegantly performed\, and artfully minimised movies in any genre\; use of 
 obsolete technologies\, creative compression techniques\, and low-bandwidt
 h aesthetics at all stages of production is encouraged. Resources for maki
 ng small-file work at www.smallfile.ca/make. Open to artists\, activists\,
  media pirates\, rogue technologists\, and filmmakers. No payment or submi
 ssion fee stated. All submitted information used for festival programming 
 and promotion -- ensure accurate spelling\, punctuation\, and capitalisati
 on. Submissions close 1 July 2026 at midnight. Submit at https://smallfile
 .ca/submit/.\n\nOrganisation: Small File Media Society\nLocation: Canada\;
  festival screening. Open to international submissions.\nAward: No payment
  stated\; festival programming and screening. No submission fee stated.\nD
 uration: One-time festival screening.\n\nMore: https://smallfile.ca/submit
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://smallfile.ca/submit/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
LOCATION:Canada\; festival screening. Open to international submissions.
END:VEVENT
