BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mountainfilm-commitment-grants-emerging-filmmaker-fellowship-2026@artif
 icialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260716
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260717
SUMMARY:Deadline: Mountainfilm: Commitment Grants & Emerging Filmmaker Fell
 owship
DESCRIPTION:Mountainfilm's Commitment Grants support documentary filmmakers
  with projects in post-production\, with over USD 90\,000 in funding this 
 cycle for films that celebrate adventure\, activism\, social justice\, cul
 ture\, the environment\, and indomitable spirit. Mountainfilm actively enc
 ourages diversity behind the camera\, and a portion of funding is set asid
 e for two focus areas: projects featuring an LGBTQ+ protagonist or a story
  about overcoming personal challenges\, societal stigmas\, and/or communit
 y obstacles with a meaningful connection to the outdoors or nature-based p
 ursuits\; and projects exploring immigration or migration\, or created by 
 immigrant or first-generation immigrant filmmakers. AWARDS: individual Com
 mitment Grants range from USD 3\,000 to 6\,000. EMERGING FILMMAKER FELLOWS
 HIP: one early-career filmmaker is selected from the Commitment Grant appl
 icant pool for a yearlong mentorship that includes edit and story consulta
 tion\, networking opportunities\, a cash award\, and a funded trip to Tell
 uride during the festival over Memorial Day weekend (travel\, lodging\, an
 d a Mountainfilm pass\, applicable to the year following the award). ELIGI
 BILITY: Commitment Grants are open to applicants from any country\; the Em
 erging Filmmaker Fellowship accepts applicants from any country but requir
 es current U.S. residency. Post-production projects only\, completed\, rel
 eased\, or festival-screened projects are not eligible\, and impact campai
 gns are not funded. Prior Commitment Grant recipients should not re-apply 
 for the same project\; previously declined projects may re-apply only with
  substantial changes. REQUIREMENTS: a video sample or trailer of the curre
 nt project no longer than 10 minutes (password-protected Vimeo links prefe
 rred)\; the screener link must stay active and cannot be changed after sub
 mission. The Emerging Filmmaker application additionally requires a direct
 or bio\, headshot\, and cover letter. Recipients are expected to provide p
 rogress updates 2-3 times a year\, include Mountainfilm recognition in cre
 dits\, and discuss premiere consideration with the programming team. TIMEL
 INE: applications are open July 1 to July 16\, 2026 (closing 11:59 PM MDT)
 \, with notifications in late August or early September. Questions: entrie
 s@mountainfilm.org.\n\nOrganisation: Mountainfilm\nLocation: Application o
 nline\; Telluride\, Colorado\, United States (fellowship trip during the f
 estival). Commitment Grants are open to filmmakers from any country\; the 
 Emerging Filmmaker Fellowship requires current U.S. residency.\nAward: Ove
 r USD 90\,000 in total funding. Individual Commitment Grants range from US
 D 3\,000 to 6\,000. The Emerging Filmmaker Fellowship adds a yearlong ment
 orship\, a cash award\, and a funded trip to Telluride over Memorial Day w
 eekend (travel\, lodging\, and a festival pass).\nDuration: Commitment Gra
 nts support projects in post-production\; the Emerging Filmmaker Fellowshi
 p is a yearlong mentorship.\n\nMore: https://www.mountainfilm.org/mountain
 film-initiatives/commitment-grants/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&
 utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.mountainfilm.org/mountainfilm-initiatives/commitment-grants
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Application online\; Telluride\, Colorado\, United States (fellows
 hip trip during the festival). Commitment Grants are open to filmmakers fr
 om any country\; the Emerging Filmmaker Fellowship requires current U.S. r
 esidency.
END:VEVENT
