BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fujifilm-gfx-challenge-grant-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260817
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260818
SUMMARY:Deadline: FUJIFILM GFX Challenge Grant Program 2026
DESCRIPTION:The GFX Challenge Grant Program\, sponsored by FUJIFILM and run
 ning since 2021\, awards 5 Global Grant Awards (USD 10\,000) and 10 Region
 al Grant Awards (USD 5\,000) to help aspiring creatives bring imaging proj
 ects to life. It is designed to nurture emerging and promising content cre
 ators\, giving them the opportunity to create content on topics with signi
 ficant meaning to them while gaining experience with FUJIFILM GFX System g
 ear\, including the GFX ETERNA 55 filmmaking camera. Proposed projects may
  be submitted as still photography or in movie format. AWARDS: both tiers 
 include complimentary use of a GFX System camera body and two GF lenses fo
 r the duration of the project\, plus mentoring and technical assistance fr
 om Fujifilm technicians and product experts. At the end of the production 
 period in May 2027\, recipients' final content is showcased on fujifilm-x.
 com\, with a series of exhibitions planned in various countries. ELIGIBILI
 TY: open to both amateur and professional photographers and videographers 
 who are residents of the countries/regions listed in the Entry Submission 
 section of the program page\; not open to employees or officers of FUJIFIL
 M and its subsidiaries. TO APPLY: combine three items into a single PDF: (
 1) the preformatted cover letter (downloadable from the program page)\; (2
 ) the project proposal covering descriptive plan\, objectives\, evaluation
  and outcome measures\, communications\, how you will use the Fujifilm par
 tnership and mentoring\, schedule\, and budget\; (3) a portfolio for each 
 individual involved. Proposals must be in English (optionally accompanied 
 by a version in your own language\; language proficiency is not judged). E
 ntry period 16 June to 17 August 2026.\n\nOrganisation: FUJIFILM\nLocation
 : Open to residents of the countries/regions listed under Entry Submission
  on the program page. Final content showcased on fujifilm-x.com plus plann
 ed exhibitions in various countries.\nAward: 5 Global Grant Awards of USD 
 10\,000 and 10 Regional Grant Awards of USD 5\,000. All recipients also ge
 t complimentary use of a GFX System camera body (including the FUJIFILM GF
 X ETERNA 55 filmmaking camera) and two GF lenses for the duration of the p
 roject\, plus mentoring and technical assistance from Fujifilm technicians
  and product experts. Total approximate retail value of all awards: USD 22
 9\,500. No purchase necessary\; no entry fee.\nDuration: Application windo
 w 16 June to 17 August 2026. Production period concludes in May 2027\, aft
 er which final content is showcased on fujifilm-x.com and in a planned ser
 ies of exhibitions.\n\nMore: https://www.fujifilm-x.com/global/gfx-challen
 ge-grant-program/year-2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medi
 um=referral
URL:https://www.fujifilm-x.com/global/gfx-challenge-grant-program/year-2026
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Open to residents of the countries/regions listed under Entry Subm
 ission on the program page. Final content showcased on fujifilm-x.com plus
