  media arts\, performance\, sound and moving image. The two-month residenc
 y comes with an artist fee of CHF 2\,000 per month\, a CHF 15\,000 product
 ion grant to develop a new work or continue an existing project (open to a
 ll formats\, building on the residency research)\, and travel and accommod
 ation for the festival and residency\; the project must be completed by De
 cember 2027. The 2027 programme (transmediale's 40th anniversary\, themed 
 'RFC 40' after the early-internet Request for Comments documents) seeks pr
 oposals offering alternatives to how we understand\, respond to and shape 
 our technological conditions\, moving from critique to construction outsid
 e extractive logics. ELIGIBILITY: applicants must have Swiss nationality o
 r permanent residence in Switzerland\, be firmly established in the Swiss 
 cultural scene\, and meet Pro Helvetia's general requirements\; duos and c
 ollectives welcome (fee and grant shared). Deadline: 28 August 2026\, 23:5
 9 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: transmediale (in cooperation with the Swiss Arts 
